p:
Avocado (
 Persea americana Mill) is a rich oil fruit of high economic importance in the international trade. Its nutritional value has been lately highlighted: it is a rich source of monounsaturated and polyunsaturated fatty acids associated with a decreased risk of cardiovascular diseases (
 Mendez and Hernandez, 2007; 
 Rodriguez-Sanchez et al., 2015). It is also an important source of vitamins A, B, and C and minerals such as potassium, phosphorus, magnesium, iron, and a rich source of fiber and antioxidants (
 Villa-Rodriguez et al., 2011; 
 Dreher and Davenport, 2013; 
 Bill et al., 2014).
